before we go out there.

07:16.418 --> 07:18.536
Hold on, Mr. Shue. Hold on.
You've given us

07:18.620 --> 07:20.922
a lot of pep talks
over the years, but remember,

07:20.989 --> 07:22.540
you told us once
that, you know,

07:22.624 --> 07:27.328
a teacher's job is done when his
students don't need him anymore?

07:27.379 --> 07:32.133
Okay. Finn, the floor is yours.

07:32.184 --> 07:34.302
Last night we all sat around
in a circle

07:34.353 --> 07:36.337
after you went to bed
and we told stories.

07:36.388 --> 07:38.105
But then we went around
the room,

07:38.173 --> 07:40.691
and everybody said what they
wanted to win this thing for,

07:40.776 --> 07:42.560
and we all said the same thing:

07:42.644 --> 07:44.946
we want to win this for you.
Yeah.

07:45.013 --> 07:47.231
And I know every year at school
Figgins gives away

07:47.316 --> 07:50.017
the Teacher of the Year award.

07:50.068 --> 07:52.453
But I don't think
any of us have to wait

07:52.520 --> 07:54.521
to see how we feel about that.

07:54.573 --> 07:57.241
You're, like, our
Teacher of a Lifetime.

07:57.326 --> 07:58.209
GIRL:
Yeah.

07:58.293 --> 08:00.244
Whoo!
Yeah, definitely.

08:00.329 --> 08:02.529
Thank you, Finn, all of you.

08:02.581 --> 08:03.881
I love you guys so much.

08:03.966 --> 08:05.866
